Finally, in the last days of October, Merkel appeared again with a clear position, when she demanded to reform the conventions of the European Union in such a way that it would be possible to rescue a member state and, at the same time, that private creditors would be obliged to bear part of the costs.
This position was interpreted as anti-European as it precipitated the Irish crisis and everything else.
