The year 2013 will mark the birth of a new currency area, in which states that break the rules will be severely sanctioned and may be forced to report deferred payments, and the private sector will also have to bear some of the costs.
Germany suggests that we must take a strict growth path with increased savings and investment rates, moderate consumption, improved productivity and competitiveness, and capital reserves.
Another option based on claims and construction, with huge balance of payments gaps, such as prevailed during Spain&#39;s boom years, they are simply not going to tolerate.
