Prime Minister Zapatero seems to have understood this as well, and his double announcement (reforms promised after last Saturday&#39;s meeting with big business and yesterday&#39;s announcement of new measures) suggests that criticism of Merkel has opened the way to the idea that things need to be put in ok
But the red line that Germany drew is here, and it doesn&#39;t seem like it wants to move.
And from the options that can be considered, leaving the eurozone, which is full of not very serious countries, cannot be excluded.
