The country&#39;s representative at the COP16 UN climate change conference assured that his country has made extraordinary efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and specified that it is sticking to its promise to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45% by 2020.
China will keep its promise to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45% in 2020, assured Su Wei, the country&#39;s representative at the UN Climate Change Conference.
In his first public appearance at the 16th Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change, Su Wei assured that his country has made immense efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and transform its industry.
